                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1858" source="#bib1858-2\1">In hagiography: <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1858">The Maccabees</persName> were seven sons who along with their mother, <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2080">Shamuni</persName>, were the victims of persecution and proto-martyrdom as told in the book of <title>2 Maccabees</title>. In the Syriac account, they were martyred in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/10">Antioch</placeName> in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/486">Syria</placeName>.</note>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1858-1">
